@startuml sandbox
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title Sandbox — isolation tests-code slice 2d (Dαα, opt-in, fail-closed)

package "src/main/modelhub/routing/sandbox/" {
  component "index.ts\n• getSandbox({enabled})\n• dispatch par\n  process.platform" as IDX
  component "types.ts\n• SandboxProvider (ABC)\n• SandboxResult\n• SandboxOptions\n• SandboxUnavailable" as TYPES

  component "unsafe.ts\n• UnsafeSandbox\n• throw à chaque fois\n• défaut quand opt-in off" as UNSAFE
  component "posix.ts\n• PosixSandbox\n• rlimits NPROC=cur,\n  AS/DATA=512 MiB,\n  CPU=10s, FSIZE=0\n• pgrp détaché\n• kill -pgid sur timeout\n• `python -I -S -B`" as POSIX
  component "windows.ts\n• WindowsSandbox\n• dispatche vers PS1" as WIN
  component "win-job.ps1\n• Add-Type P/Invoke\n• CreateJobObject\n• ActiveProcessLimit=1\n• ProcessMemoryLimit\n  =512 MiB\n• KILL_ON_JOB_CLOSE\n• streams marker-line" as PS1
}

component "characterizeRunner.ts\n(construit le seam runSandbox)" as RUNNER
component "staircase.evaluateItem()\n(catch le throw ⇒ UNMEASURED)" as STAIR

RUNNER --> IDX : getSandbox({enabled})
IDX --> UNSAFE : enabled:false\n(défaut) OU\nOS inconnu
IDX --> POSIX : enabled:true\n+ linux/darwin
IDX --> WIN : enabled:true\n+ win32

WIN --> PS1 : spawn powershell.exe\n-File win-job.ps1
POSIX ..> "python3\n(enfant)" : spawn\ndetached:true
PS1 ..> "python.exe\n(enfant)" : Process.Start +\nAssignProcessToJobObject

UNSAFE -.-> STAIR : throw\nSandboxUnavailable
POSIX -.-> STAIR : {pass:bool} OU\nthrow sur\nUNMEASURED
WIN -.-> STAIR : {pass:bool} OU\nthrow sur\nUNMEASURED

note bottom of IDX
  Fail-closed (Dαα §3) :
  TOUTE impossibilité d'établir
  la frontière kernel ⇒ throw
  SandboxUnavailable ⇒ l'appelant
  marque l'item UNMEASURED.
  **Jamais** un faux pass.
end note

note right of POSIX
  Préambule défense-en-profondeur bloque
  les imports (socket, subprocess,
  ctypes, …) — trivialement contournable,
  les rlimits SONT la frontière.
end note

@enduml
